75 meters from the water and twelve minutes from town is our gable row house. Kvista down for a morning swim from the nearest jetty, or take a short walk to Hökarängsbadet with beach and cafe.

By bus you are in Södermalm in almost a quarter, with shopping, restaurants and crowds. From there, Stockholm is wide open and you can easily get around to museums, sights, or why not Gröna Lund.

Garden with barbecue and several seating pits is available, and a terrace with sea glimpses of course.

name: Superior Queen
description: Nestled in Vasastan, Clas på hörnet Hotel revitalizes an 18th-century tavern into a sophisticated boutique, preserving original details and craftsmanship. Our 24 rooms, individually furnished, provide a home-away-from-home. The modern design with vintage accents defines seven distinctive room categories. Well planned family friendly villa of 163 sqm in very good location in Bromma with place for a big family.

Sunny garden, two terraces, two barbecues, trampoline.

From the house it takes about 20 minutes to get to Stockholm city.
Proximity to swimming
WiFi (500 MBit)

Peaceful apartment close to nature and yet also close to the city. Perfect for a family who wants to make excursions during the day and have quiet evenings in a quiet, quiet area with nature reserve that starts right outside the door.
It only takes 30 minutes with the subway into the city center.

One bedroom has a 120 cm wide bed and the other has a 140 cm bed.

The kitchen is big and the dining table has seating for five people.
There is a dishwasher and all other equipment.
In the bathroom there is also a washing machine.

name: Fantastic apartment in Södermalm
description: Welcome to our charming turn-of-the-century apartment in the heart of Södermalm. This 55-square-meter space features large windows overlooking both the lively street and a tranquil courtyard complete with a boules court for your enjoyment. It's been fully renovated while keeping charming original details like the tile stove. It's situated between Nytorget and Mosebacke, two of Stockholm's most vibrant areas. 150 meters away, the subway will take you to the city center in only 6 minutes.
